]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ISU welcomes the decision of CAS and firmly maintains its position that the protection of clean athletes and the fight against doping are of the highest priority and will persist in the ongoing effort to uphold the integrity of fair competition and the well-being of athletes,\\\" the skating body said.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8773062662599316e-55, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"its position\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"the protection\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"clean athletes\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"the fight\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest priority\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1158}, {\"ngram\": \"the ongoing effort\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"the integrity\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"fair competition\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1241}, {\"ngram\": \"the well-being\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"the skating body\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ISU is in close contact with the International Olympic Committee (IOC) and the relevant ISU member federations in regard to the implementation of this decision.\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1390, \"end\": 1393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"close contact\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"regard\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"the implementation\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"this decision\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It added that the decision meant Vasilyeva was disqualified from her fourth-place showing in the women's singles event in Beijing, and from her first-place finish at the European Championships in 2022.The Russian Olympic Committee (ROC) said on January 30 it would appeal the ISU decision to strip it of an Olympic gold medal, stressing that its lawyers were preparing to contest the decision.\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_O