licable regulations, consequences of the decision to impose sanctions on an individual athlete, in this case Kamila Valiyeva, cannot be grounds for a revision of the results of the team tournament.\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1907, \"end\": 1910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.653189217115038e-41, \"text\": \"ISU\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Skating_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our position\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"consequences\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1962}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"sanctions\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual athlete\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"grounds\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"a revision\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"the results\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2102}, {\"ngram\": \"the team tournament\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our legal standpoint is also based on existing precedents in CAS practice,\\\" the ROCsaidin a statement.Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov said Russia should use \\\"any opportunities to challenge\\\" the decision and \\\"defend our athletes' rights.\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8773062662599316e-55, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso